						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Sorry, you guys are correct, I meant to say 5th overall, not 5th rounder.  I'd be fine with him coming back on a try-out basis but only if his current contract is torn up and then burned.  If he wants to try to make the team (as a guard or tackle) and takes the league minimum with incentives for playing time that'd be great.  But as a guy who's now lost multiple seasons and was a cast off from another team not all that long after they took him in the first round; he is not worth all that much.  And since he never even played a game w/ the Steelers it's not as if he has a leg up on the playbook/schemes more so than a healthy FA they could look to bring in.  My main point is I don't believe this guy is in any way the answer to the line issues.  If he's willing to play on the cheap he might be a complimentary player.  Might.
						</blockquote>
