							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>bowldog</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=678e964a69cc7c1b97b5b3e47f008a29&amp;p=579314#post579314" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">You guys do realize that at the start of the season our OL had the least number of starts of any line in the league. Short of getting our Qb killed (Adams) give these guys a chance to gel. The way you guys talk on this board everybody has to be perfect, every game has to be perfect, every offensive play has to be perfect, every defensive play has to be perfect, every special teams play has to be perfect, the owner,gm, coaches have to be perfect. These are people not robots. If Brady and P Manning are so GREAT how come between both of them they have only won ONE SB in the last 10 years and Ben has TWO. Lighten up already,we all have high expectations of our team. We got to 2 TO last game BUT because we dropped one that is the story people run with. enough</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I agree with what you are saying, which is why I hate the constant movement of the OL during the summer.  Adams and Gilbert flipped sides, trying everyone at every different position - guards at center etc.<br />
<br />
When it comes to the OL, I'd like to see the coaches determine their starting five and then keep them together, side-by-side, throughout the spring and summer.  This is where they have to earn their paychecks - by evaluating who will be their best and then doing everything they can to make that happen.
